---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/page-intro.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="research · colin vargas"
  description="research interests and computational fluid dynamics work by colin vargas."
  active="research"
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="research / computational physics"
    title="modeling messy flow physics without pretending the world is polite."
    description="my research interests sit at the intersection of numerical methods, computational fluid dynamics, propulsion, combustion, and adaptive simulation."
  />

  <section class="research-layout">
    <article class="surface-panel main-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">primary direction</p>
      <h2>adaptive cfd solver development</h2>

      <p>
        my current direction is focused on building toward higher-fidelity cfd tools
        that can handle more realistic aerospace and propulsion problems. the goal is
        to move beyond clean academic examples and toward simulations that can support
        complex flow behavior, non-ideal assumptions, and eventually combustion-relevant
        physics.
      </p>

      <p>
        the foundation is numerical method development: finite-volume discretization,
        advection schemes, conservation diagnostics, grid refinement, and verification
        workflows. from there, the long-term path points toward navier-stokes,
        turbulence modeling, multiphase effects, evaporation, and gas-turbine-relevant
        applications.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="surface-panel side-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">research stack</p>

      <ul class="tag-list">
        <li>c++</li>
        <li>python</li>
        <li>amrex</li>
        <li>paraview</li>
        <li>finite volume</li>
        <li>adaptive mesh refinement</li>
        <li>numerical verification</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="timeline-list">
    <article class="surface-panel resume-entry">
      <p class="eyebrow">01 / solver foundations</p>
      <h2>advection and conservation</h2>
      <p>
        building the base layer for scalar transport, flux evaluation, periodic boundaries,
        mass conservation checks, and grid refinement studies.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="surface-panel resume-entry">
      <p class="eyebrow">02 / amr infrastructure</p>
      <h2>adaptive mesh refinement</h2>
      <p>
        integrating amr concepts to resolve important flow features efficiently instead
        of spending compute everywhere like a caveman with a cluster allocation.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="surface-panel resume-entry">
      <p class="eyebrow">03 / propulsion relevance</p>
      <h2>combustion and gas-turbine flows</h2>
      <p>
        long-term interest in applying high-fidelity flow models to fuel injection,
        evaporation, combustion, and turbine-engine-relevant physics.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
